Based on my research of the FireCut deobfuscated code, here are the findings:

---

## 1. Podcast Audio Sync - Audio Track Linking

FireCut does NOT implement waveform-based audio alignment. Instead, it uses a **position-based linking** approach:

**File:** `/Users/imorgado/Desktop/Fireside_Deobstuficated/firecut_host_decoded.jsx`
**Lines:** 271-291

```javascript
function linkIdenticalClipsInTracks(videoTrackIndex, audioTrackIndex) {
    var selected_clips = app.project.activeSequence.getSelection();
    for (var i = 0; i < selected_clips.length; i += 1) { 
        selected_clips[i].setSelected(false, false);
    }
    var video_clips = app.project.activeSequence.videoTracks[videoTrackIndex].clips;
    var audio_clips = app.project.activeSequence.audioTracks[audioTrackIndex].clips;
    for (var i = 0; i < video_clips.length; i += 1) { 
        var video_clip = video_clips[i];
        var video_start = video_clip.start.seconds;
        for (var j = 0; j < audio_clips.length; j += 1) { 
            var audio_clip = audio_clips[j];
            var audio_start = audio_clip.start.seconds;
            if (video_start == audio_start) { 
                video_clip.setSelected(true, false);
                audio_clip.setSelected(true, false);
                app.project.activeSequence.linkSelection();
                video_clip.setSelected(false, false);
                audio_clip.setSelected(false, false);
                break;
            }
        }
    }
}
```

**Algorithm:** Simple start-time comparison - if video clip and audio clip have the same `start.seconds`, they are linked together using `app.project.activeSequence.linkSelection()`.

---

## 2. J-Cut Implementation

FireCut implements J-cuts by **shifting all audio clips** before cutting, then shifting them back after.

### UI Parameters
**File:** `/Users/imorgado/Desktop/Fireside_Deobstuficated/Silence/ui_b.js`
**Lines:** 50-51, 109-110

```javascript
silence_cutting_parameters['jcuts'] = $('#checkbox-jcuts').is(':checked');
silence_cutting_parameters['jcut_offset_frames'] = parseFloat($('#range-silence-cutting-advanced-jcut-offset').val());
```

### Frame-to-Seconds Conversion
**File:** `/Users/imorgado/Desktop/Fireside_Deobstuficated/Silence/main_b.js`
**Lines:** 1129-1141

```javascript
let j_cut = silence_cutting_parameters.jcuts && silence_cutting_parameters.jcut_offset_frames > 0;
let j_cut_seconds = 0;
